File: SAA business rescue practitioners say its fast running out of cash to carry on with the rescue process. JOHANNESBURG - SAA needs money, and they need it by next week. The airline's business rescue practitioners say its fast running out of cash to carry on with the rescue process. READ: Government receives 10 offers for SAA, subsidiaries They say there is little money left to continue operations. R10.1-billion is needed to save the airline and R2.2-billion of that will go towards severance packages. READ: SAA approves over 3,000 voluntary severance package The practitioners are also still trying to finalise the termination of aircraft leases -- 33 of the 40 aircraft it leases have already been terminated. The termination of the remaining aircraft is set to be finalised by the end of September.